info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Statement issued August 30 at 9:31AM EDT until August 30 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD STATEMENT IN EFFECT... ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IS CANCELLED... * WHAT...Minor saltwater flooding peaking at around 1 foot above mean high tide. * WHERE...Middle Keys. * WHEN...Coastal Flood Statements may need to be extended into Thursday or Friday. * IMPACTS...Minor saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is likely. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: Do not drive through flooded roadways.
